1
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:39,890
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:42,039
[Episode 16]

3
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:01,820
Want a haircut?

4
00:02:02,820 --> 00:02:03,740
Taking a look.

5
00:02:06,170 --> 00:02:07,370
At what?

6
00:02:09,979 --> 00:02:10,720
Nothing.

7
00:02:13,470 --> 00:02:13,870
Uncle!

8
00:02:13,890 --> 00:02:14,390
Uncle!

9
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:17,020
I found him!

10
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:19,260
He's in that barbershop we just passed.

11
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:20,860
What's he wearing?

12
00:02:20,860 --> 00:02:22,120
What does he look like?

13
00:02:22,470 --> 00:02:23,590
I didn't really notice

14
00:02:23,590 --> 00:02:25,300
what he's wearing.

15
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:26,560
He's big and burly,

16
00:02:26,579 --> 00:02:28,240
and wearing a silver earring.

17
00:02:29,220 --> 00:02:30,920
Okay. Go home.

18
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,200
Wait, you're going alone?

19
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:32,870
Go home.

20
00:03:08,820 --> 00:03:10,310
Was it you who led the attack on Xie Wanghe,

21
00:03:10,310 --> 00:03:12,560
that student from No. 7 High School?

22
00:03:15,510 --> 00:03:16,930
Yes. What about it?

23
00:03:18,110 --> 00:03:19,640
Why did you guys beat him up?

24
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,480
I didn't like the look of him.

25
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,730
What's the problem?

26
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:27,320
That was a bit brutal, no?

27
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:31,150
Let me.

28
00:03:35,630 --> 00:03:36,290
Who are you?

29
00:03:37,570 --> 00:03:39,190
Me? My surname is Xie too.

30
00:03:39,970 --> 00:03:40,990
What's your name?

31
00:03:41,470 --> 00:03:42,740
My surname is Tong.

32
00:03:43,110 --> 00:03:44,520
Go ask around sometime.

33
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:47,440
Everyone in this neighborhood knows me.

34
00:03:50,790 --> 00:03:52,530
Tong as in "child"?

35
00:03:52,829 --> 00:03:53,630
That's right.

36
00:03:53,829 --> 00:03:54,829
One name

37
00:03:54,850 --> 00:03:56,160
and one name only.

38
00:03:56,180 --> 00:03:57,640
Tong San of Flower Street.

39
00:04:07,070 --> 00:04:07,730
Come on!

40
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:18,880
You and your dad are still not talking?

41
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,510
What's the big grudge between you two?

42
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:21,510
You talk too much.

43
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:27,470
This has expired.

44
00:04:32,270 --> 00:04:34,470
Why are you still eating it? Are you stupid?

45
00:04:34,470 --> 00:04:35,270
It won't kill me.

46
00:04:35,270 --> 00:04:36,070
I'm starving.

47
00:04:37,430 --> 00:04:37,830
Here.

48
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:39,310
Have this too.

49
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:41,909
Go home after you finish.

50
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:51,090
I'll take my time then.

51
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:55,010
Causing trouble for me again!

52
00:04:55,010 --> 00:04:55,990
Causing trouble for me again!

53
00:04:55,990 --> 00:04:57,320
What are you doing, dad?

54
00:04:58,420 --> 00:04:59,110
What are you...

55
00:04:59,110 --> 00:04:59,870
I'll knock some sense into you!

56
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:01,270
Why are you beating me?

57
00:05:01,290 --> 00:05:02,850
You're causing trouble again!

58
00:05:02,850 --> 00:05:04,690
Going around causing trouble!

59
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:06,340
Every single day!

60
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:07,950
This is what you get

61
00:05:08,270 --> 00:05:09,470
for causing trouble!

62
00:05:09,630 --> 00:05:10,620
Come here now!

63
00:05:10,990 --> 00:05:11,730
Come here!

64
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:12,930
Come out!

65
00:05:15,570 --> 00:05:16,020
What are you doing?

66
00:05:16,020 --> 00:05:16,820
On your knees!

67
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:18,280
Kneel properly.

68
00:05:18,630 --> 00:05:19,290
Kneel!

69
00:05:19,630 --> 00:05:20,280
Kneel properly!

70
00:05:20,130 --> 00:05:22,380
[Billiards]

71
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,810
Mr. Xie,

72
00:05:27,580 --> 00:05:28,690
I'm sorry.

73
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,650
I didn't do a good job disciplining this brat.

74
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,270
My wife passed away early.

75
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:34,350
I've been too busy earning a living.

76
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:35,510
I didn't have time.

77
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:37,720
How is your son now?

78
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:41,030
His ribs are injured.

79
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:43,870
And his left arm has a fracture.

80
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,740
Well done, you.

81
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:51,909
How much are the medical expenses?

82
00:05:51,909 --> 00:05:52,830
Just give me the bill,

83
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:55,360
and I'll transfer the money to you right away.

84
00:05:56,270 --> 00:05:57,680
Money is not the issue.

85
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:00,280
He needs to apologize.

86
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:03,960
You heard that?

87
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:05,350
I did. I did, Dad.

88
00:06:05,350 --> 00:06:06,220
I did.

89
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:25,060
Have some soup.

90
00:06:25,570 --> 00:06:27,610
My mom made pork trotter soup.

91
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:29,270
She added eucommia and goji berries.

92
00:06:29,270 --> 00:06:31,070
Great for strengthening bones.

93
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:32,080
Is it any good?

94
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,730
Try it out.

95
00:06:39,050 --> 00:06:39,810
Not bad.

96
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,080
Let me.

97
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:43,670
It's okay,

98
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:44,380
-I'll help myself.
-Let me.

99
00:06:44,380 --> 00:06:45,380
I'll help myself.

100
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,140
Don't stand on ceremony.

101
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:51,090
You got beaten up because of me.

102
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:51,700
Now you're injured,

103
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:53,120
I must look after you.

104
00:06:55,830 --> 00:06:56,360
How is it?

105
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:58,250
A bit higher.

106
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:03,310
Fenghua,

107
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:06,940
are you actually happy that I got beaten up?

108
00:07:07,820 --> 00:07:09,930
Or why else would you be smiling?

109
00:07:10,190 --> 00:07:12,450
If you want to laugh, just laugh out loud.

110
00:07:15,910 --> 00:07:17,550
Yes, I am happy.

111
00:07:17,570 --> 00:07:19,420
I'm gloating, okay?

112
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:21,560
That's what you get for your loose tongue.

113
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,560
Serves you right!

114
00:07:23,620 --> 00:07:24,750
Aren't you the same?

115
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:26,120
Mine is self-defense.

116
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:29,390
You're the one who starts it every time.

117
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:30,690
Fine.

118
00:07:30,830 --> 00:07:32,140
I won't start anything from now on.

119
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:33,700
I'll avoid you when I see you.

120
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:35,020
And you'll stop telling me about your troubles.

121
00:07:35,020 --> 00:07:35,730
Fine, fine.

122
00:07:35,770 --> 00:07:36,750
Fine, fine.

123
00:07:36,909 --> 00:07:38,230
Blabbering non-stop.

124
00:07:38,230 --> 00:07:40,020
Even injuries can't shut you up.

125
00:07:40,020 --> 00:07:41,430
Can't you be a little gentler?

126
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:42,490
Seriously, you...

127
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:44,360
Siyi.

128
00:07:45,450 --> 00:07:47,290
Want some soup? Pork trotter soup.

129
00:07:47,290 --> 00:07:48,370
I'm okay.

130
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:49,630
Are you alright?

131
00:07:49,630 --> 00:07:50,750
My grandma said you were injured.

132
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:51,230
I'm fine.

133
00:07:51,230 --> 00:07:51,909
He's fine.

134
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,990
It's only terminal cancer. He won't die.

135
00:07:53,990 --> 00:07:55,690
Shut up, will you?

136
00:07:56,150 --> 00:07:58,230
If I die someday, it'll be because of your curse.

137
00:07:58,230 --> 00:07:58,830
Honestly.

138
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:02,630
Why don't you ever learn?

139
00:08:02,910 --> 00:08:04,230
Can't you say something auspicious?

140
00:08:04,230 --> 00:08:04,830
You...

141
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:05,820
You...

142
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,540
You've gotten quite bold, haven't you?

143
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:08,350
-Let go!
-Let go!

144
00:08:08,350 --> 00:08:08,910
You do it first.

145
00:08:08,910 --> 00:08:09,510
You first.

146
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:10,260
Three.

147
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:11,030
Two.

148
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:17,490
It's very good. Have some.

149
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:19,810
You have some more. It's good for you.

150
00:08:20,030 --> 00:08:21,160
Well, I'll...

151
00:08:22,030 --> 00:08:23,210
Hang with us for a while?

152
00:08:23,210 --> 00:08:23,900
It's okay.

153
00:08:24,070 --> 00:08:25,440
I've got homework to do.

154
00:08:25,550 --> 00:08:26,150
Take care.

155
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:27,910
Siyi.

156
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,140
Good night.

157
00:08:31,220 --> 00:08:31,960
Good night.

158
00:08:43,909 --> 00:08:44,470
Siyi.

159
00:08:49,010 --> 00:08:50,770
It's just a bone fracture.

160
00:08:50,810 --> 00:08:51,950
Don't worry.

161
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:55,320
Take good care of him.

162
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:56,670
Let me know if anything.

163
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:59,420
How about you take over tomorrow?

164
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,470
No.

165
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,940
I'm clumsy and not patient enough.

166
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,570
You're much better at this.

167
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:11,520
Keep it up.

168
00:10:37,940 --> 00:10:38,500
Hurry up.

169
00:10:39,650 --> 00:10:40,580
On it.

170
00:10:40,610 --> 00:10:41,940
What do you mean "on it"?

171
00:10:42,390 --> 00:10:43,310
Hurry up!

172
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:46,270
Hurry!

173
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,430
Listen.

174
00:10:48,350 --> 00:10:50,160
Apologize properly when you go in there.

175
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:52,130
You'll look after him for the rest
of his life if it's serious.

176
00:10:52,130 --> 00:10:53,310
You little brat.

177
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:54,660
Always up to no good.

178
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:55,950
Causing trouble for me all the time!

179
00:10:55,950 --> 00:10:56,850
Alright.

180
00:10:57,310 --> 00:10:58,230
Stop shouting.

181
00:10:58,250 --> 00:10:58,910
We're here.

182
00:11:06,780 --> 00:11:07,490
Wanghe,

183
00:11:08,070 --> 00:11:09,130
you have a visitor.

184
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:28,720
What's going on?

185
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:29,800
What's with all this racket?

186
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:30,820
No idea.

187
00:11:32,070 --> 00:11:33,680
You know him, right?

188
00:11:40,390 --> 00:11:41,500
I'm sorry, Xie.

189
00:11:42,070 --> 00:11:42,890
I did wrong.

190
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:45,860
You beat him up like that,

191
00:11:45,860 --> 00:11:47,300
and you think a simple "sorry" will do?

192
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:48,560
I won't beat him again.

193
00:11:49,330 --> 00:11:50,880
If I break your bones

194
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,930
and casually say "sorry" to you,

195
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,020
will you let me off?

196
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:58,580
This is a society governed by law.

197
00:11:58,870 --> 00:12:00,790
You've beaten Wanghe to this state.

198
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:02,760
If we don't accept mediation,

199
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:05,230
you'll end up in jail, you know that?

200
00:12:05,270 --> 00:12:06,370
Did you hear that?

201
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,540
I did.

202
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,670
From now on, when I see Xie,

203
00:12:11,090 --> 00:12:12,380
I'll keep out of his way.

204
00:12:12,380 --> 00:12:12,910
Get lost!

205
00:12:18,430 --> 00:12:20,030
I'm really sorry about this.

206
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:23,910
What's your problem?

207
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:24,790
Seriously.

208
00:12:24,830 --> 00:12:25,590
Mr. Xie,

209
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:26,920
I'm really sorry.

210
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:29,100
If you need anything else later,
just let me know.

211
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:30,840
This kid came to apologize.

212
00:12:35,540 --> 00:12:36,230
Maotian.

213
00:12:37,170 --> 00:12:38,220
It's been a while.

214
00:12:38,470 --> 00:12:38,950
I'm sorry.

215
00:12:38,950 --> 00:12:39,950
My son...

216
00:12:40,330 --> 00:12:41,550
Well, if you'll excuse me.

217
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:42,070
Okay.

218
00:12:45,210 --> 00:12:46,190
Alright, we're done.

219
00:12:46,190 --> 00:12:46,920
All settled.

220
00:12:47,660 --> 00:12:48,720
You can go back now.

221
00:12:49,190 --> 00:12:49,810
Uncle Xie.

222
00:12:51,780 --> 00:12:52,310
Get lost.

223
00:12:55,110 --> 00:12:55,550
Bye, Auntie.

224
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:56,080
Bye, Uncle.

225
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:56,940
What are you having?

226
00:12:56,940 --> 00:12:57,950
Home-style tofu.

227
00:12:58,060 --> 00:12:58,670
Tofu.

228
00:12:58,670 --> 00:12:59,730
You had dinner yet?

229
00:12:59,740 --> 00:13:00,700
I've got bread.

230
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:03,590
Fenghua.

231
00:13:04,090 --> 00:13:05,990
Make sure he takes his meds.

232
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:07,560
They're paying

233
00:13:07,570 --> 00:13:08,830
all the medical bills.

234
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:10,510
And that guy,

235
00:13:10,510 --> 00:13:11,950
Hai,

236
00:13:11,950 --> 00:13:13,150
is now in custody.

237
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:15,890
Let's consider this as settled now.

238
00:13:16,310 --> 00:13:17,810
If we don't accept mediation,

239
00:13:17,810 --> 00:13:19,470
they will have to pay even more.

240
00:13:19,470 --> 00:13:21,670
We could send that guy straight to jail.

241
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:23,110
That would create a feud.

242
00:13:23,110 --> 00:13:23,710
Not ideal.

243
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:26,830
You're very generous indeed.

244
00:13:26,830 --> 00:13:28,090
If this happened to me,

245
00:13:28,230 --> 00:13:29,830
my mom would try to kill them.

246
00:13:30,590 --> 00:13:33,540
We used to run ships on the same canal.

247
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:35,780
There's no need to make things so tense.

248
00:13:40,350 --> 00:13:42,030
Oh, Wanghe,

249
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:45,250
don't let your mom know about this.

250
00:13:45,670 --> 00:13:46,720
Just tell her

251
00:13:46,990 --> 00:13:49,140
you got injured playing basketball.

252
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:51,530
I was thinking the same thing.

253
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:55,260
Why?

254
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:57,710
Your mom would try to kill them.

255
00:13:57,710 --> 00:13:58,700
So would my mom.

256
00:14:00,790 --> 00:14:02,670
As if things aren't bad enough already.

257
00:14:02,670 --> 00:14:03,600
Give me the meds.

258
00:14:05,350 --> 00:14:05,910
Go home.

259
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:07,470
Wait.

260
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,730
Can you manage on your own?

261
00:14:09,830 --> 00:14:10,780
I'll be fine.

262
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,810
Remember to take your meds.

263
00:14:14,050 --> 00:14:15,370
Almost forgot my bowl.

264
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,160
Uncle, I'm off!

265
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:33,300
Dad.

266
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,620
Who is this Xie guy?

267
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:37,550
Why are you so afraid of him?

268
00:14:38,770 --> 00:14:39,570
It's not fear.

269
00:14:40,070 --> 00:14:40,870
It's respect.

270
00:14:41,590 --> 00:14:42,350
Why?

271
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,400
When we were young and making a living on ships,

272
00:14:49,470 --> 00:14:50,450
the upstream guys

273
00:14:50,450 --> 00:14:51,450
ganged up on us.

274
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,270
Boss Xie decided it was too much

275
00:14:55,310 --> 00:14:57,640
and risked his life to seek justice for us.

276
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:59,680
He had three ribs broken.

277
00:15:07,890 --> 00:15:08,920
I owe him.

278
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,240
Many people on Flower Street

279
00:15:11,580 --> 00:15:12,580
owe him.

280
00:15:38,820 --> 00:15:41,250
The once much revered "Water Dragon King"

281
00:15:41,670 --> 00:15:42,870
is now

282
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:45,370
like a piece of driftwood fallen from a ship.

283
00:15:45,590 --> 00:15:47,940
Drifting aimlessly all day long,

284
00:15:48,340 --> 00:15:50,870
without any direction for the journey.

285
00:15:52,030 --> 00:15:52,740
My dad

286
00:15:53,550 --> 00:15:54,430
is dejected.

287
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:57,730
My mom is sticking it out alone for the family.

288
00:15:58,250 --> 00:15:59,500
I wonder

289
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:01,420
when this kind of life

290
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:03,390
is going to end for us.

291
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:32,670
Seven seven zero nine five.

292
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:33,610
This is the one.

